cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.NE, cs.SY

The paper proposes a neural network approach for identifying individual electrical appliances from their consumption profiles. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The use of high-resolution measurements and raw current and voltage waveforms suggests a focus on signal processing and data analysis, which are covered by the cs.SD sub-category. The evaluation of the proposed model on a publicly available dataset and the study of model stability suggest a focus on experimental validation and system analysis, which are covered by the cs.SY sub-category. Finally, the use of neural network ensembles suggests a focus on ensemble learning and model combination, which are covered by the cs.NE sub-category.
